It's all systems go for South Africa's biggest retailer to acquire some stores belonging to Massmart. (eNCA\Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - The country’s largest retailer Shoprite would have increased its interim profits by 30 percent instead of 10 had it not been for power cuts, according to CEO Pieter Engelbrecht. Shoprite managed double-digit sales growth in the six months to January. READ: SONA 2023 | Big business wants tax relief Customers spent about R12-billion more at the retailer than in the same period a year before. But Engelbrecht says power cuts are ruining the entire economic value chain.